## 4. Integrity Clause (Core Principle)

The Software (Lihuo Protocol) is designed to:

> Prevent the stabilization of incorrect answers, not to generate answers.

Any modification, deployment, or usage that:

- Intentionally bypasses failure detection mechanisms
- Forces output completion under uncertainty
- Removes or weakens structural constraints (e.g., PATH, STOP, FAIL-STOP)

shall be considered a violation of this license.

